{{For|the official of the Helvetic Republic|Hans Caspar Hirzel (1746-1827)}} [[File:HirzelHC.jpg|thumb|right|Hirzel (in 1787?)]] '''Hans Caspar Hirzel''' (21 March 1725 - 18 February 1803), also known or spelt as - '''Herzil John Caspar''', '''Kaspar Hirzel''', '''Johann Kasper Herzel''', or '''John Kaspar Hirzel''' -, was an eminent [[Swiss people|Swiss]] physician and writer on [[Economy|rural economy]]. <ref name="R1">{{cite book |last= Gorton |first= John |title= A general biographical dictionary, Volume 2 |publisher= Whittaker and Co |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=vlwMAAAAYAAJ&pg=PT198 |year= 1833 |accessdate= February 21, 2012}}</ref><ref name="R2">{{cite book |last= Hans |first= Caspar Hirzel|author2=Arthur Young|title= Rural economy|publisher= Printed by Isaac Neale |url= https://books.google.com/books/about/Rural_economy.html?id=L1lbzgAACAAJ&redir_esc=y|year= 1792 |accessdate= February 21, 2012}}</ref>
==Biography== He was born at [[Zürich]], 1725, and adopted medical profession by his learning and intelligence. He distinguished himself in lecturing on theory and practice of medicine, including instructions to female accoucheurs. He was one of the principal founders of [[Helvetic Society]] in 1726, others were - [[Isaak Iselin]], [[Salomon Gessner]], and some 20 others.<ref name="R1"/>
He translated the works of ''Tissot'' into [[German language|German]]; subsequently, published a ''Treatise on Rural Economy'', in acquaintance with a Swiss farmer, who is distinguished for his agriculture industry and skill, Caspar Hirzel conceived the notion of publishing the result of this man's[Swiss farmer] experience in his agricultural occupation, including facts and observations from other sources. This undertaking was published as a work entitled ''The Rustic Socrates'', which had been later translated into [[English language]] by [[Arthur Young (agriculturist)|Arthur Young]], and into other languages of [[Europe]].<ref name="R1"/><ref name="R2"/><ref>{{cite book |last= Hans |first= Caspar Hirzel|author2=Arthur Young |author3=B. Vaughan |title= The rural Socrates; or An account of a celebrated philosophical farmer|publisher= Printed by Peter Edes; and sold by the booksellers in the principal towns of the United States., |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=uPg-AAAAYAAJ&pg=PA209 |year= 1800 |accessdate= February 21, 2012}}</ref>
Hirzel also authored some historical [[Eulogy|Eulogies]], also dialogues on religion and tolerance. He died of [[apoplexy]] on 19 February 1803.<ref name="R1"/>
